        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 3:25AM CDT by NWS Kansas City/Pleasant Hill MO</headline>
        <description>At 325 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Richmond, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Richmond, Polo, Henrietta, Cowgill, Rayville, and Knoxville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
